              <a href="https://book.douban.com/annotation/35625743/" class="">第77页</a></h3>
          </div>
          <div class="clst">
            <p class="user"><a href="https://www.douban.com/people/54094795/" class=" " title="Purple Man">Purple Man</a>
                (it&#39;s my two cents on the issue)
              
            </p>
            <div class="reading-note" data-cid="35625743">
              <div class="short">
                
                  <span class="">To take the third of these first: Justice Hellen analogizes the surviving spelunkers (at p. 64, above) to rape victims because they were forced to commit an act intentionally but against their will. (Is every case really about rape?)


(The last sentence is full of emotion......)</span>
                <p class="pl">
                  <span class="">2015-07-16 16:59</span>
                  
